{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"Do you worry about what is going to kill you?"},{"time":5000,"text":"Heart disease, cancer,"},{"time":7000,"text":"a car accident?"},{"time":9000,"text":"Most of us worry about things we can't control,"},{"time":12000,"text":"like war, terrorism,"},{"time":14000,"text":"the tragic earthquake that just occurred in Haiti."},{"time":17000,"text":"But what really threatens humanity?"},{"time":21000,"text":"A few years ago, Professor Vaclav Smil"},{"time":23000,"text":"tried to calculate the probability"},{"time":25000,"text":"of sudden disasters"},{"time":27000,"text":"large enough to change history."},{"time":29000,"text":"He called these,"},{"time":31000,"text":"\"massively fatal discontinuities,\""},{"time":33000,"text":"meaning that they could kill"},{"time":35000,"text":"up to 100 million people"},{"time":37000,"text":"in the next 50 years."},{"time":39000,"text":"He looked at the odds of another world war,"},{"time":42000,"text":"of a massive volcanic eruption,"},{"time":44000,"text":"even of an asteroid hitting the Earth."},{"time":46000,"text":"But he placed the likelihood of one such event"},{"time":49000,"text":"above all others"},{"time":51000,"text":"at close to 100 percent,"},{"time":53000,"text":"and that is a severe flu pandemic."},{"time":57000,"text":"Now, you might think of flu"},{"time":59000,"text":"as just a really bad cold,"},{"time":62000,"text":"but it can be a death sentence."},{"time":64000,"text":"Every year, 36,000 people in the United States"},{"time":67000,"text":"die of seasonal flu."},{"time":70000,"text":"In the developing world, the data is much sketchier"},{"time":72000,"text":"but the death toll is almost"},{"time":74000,"text":"certainly higher."},{"time":76000,"text":"You know, the problem is if"},{"time":78000,"text":"this virus occasionally mutates"},{"time":80000,"text":"so dramatically,"},{"time":82000,"text":"it essentially is a new virus"},{"time":84000,"text":"and then we get a pandemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"In 1918, a new virus appeared"},{"time":91000,"text":"that killed some 50 to 100 million people."},{"time":94000,"text":"It spread like wildfire"},{"time":96000,"text":"and some died within hours of developing symptoms."},{"time":99000,"text":"Are we safer today?"},{"time":101000,"text":"Well, we seem to have dodged"},{"time":103000,"text":"the deadly pandemic this year"},{"time":105000,"text":"that most of us feared,"},{"time":107000,"text":"but this threat could reappear at any time."},{"time":110000,"text":"The good news is that"},{"time":112000,"text":"we're at a moment in time"},{"time":114000,"text":"when science, technology, globalization is converging"},{"time":117000,"text":"to create an unprecedented possibility:"},{"time":119000,"text":"the possibility to make history"},{"time":121000,"text":"by preventing infectious diseases"},{"time":124000,"text":"that still account for one-fifth of all deaths"},{"time":127000,"text":"and countless misery on Earth."},{"time":130000,"text":"We can do this."},{"time":132000,"text":"We're already preventing millions of deaths"},{"time":134000,"text":"with existing vaccines,"},{"time":136000,"text":"and if we get these to more people,"},{"time":138000,"text":"we can certainly save more lives."},{"time":141000,"text":"But with new or better vaccines"},{"time":143000,"text":"for malaria, TB, HIV,"},{"time":146000,"text":"pneumonia, diarrhea, flu,"},{"time":148000,"text":"we could end suffering"},{"time":150000,"text":"that has been on the Earth since the beginning of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"So, I'm here to trumpet vaccines for you."},{"time":155000,"text":"But first, I have to explain why they're important"},{"time":158000,"text":"because vaccines, the power of them,"},{"time":161000,"text":"is really like a whisper."},{"time":163000,"text":"When they work, they can make history,"},{"time":165000,"text":"but after a while"},{"time":167000,"text":"you can barely hear them."},{"time":169000,"text":"Now, some of us are old enough"},{"time":172000,"text":"to have a small, circular scar on our arms"},{"time":175000,"text":"from an inoculation we received as children."},{"time":178000,"text":"But when was the last time you worried about smallpox,"},{"time":181000,"text":"a disease that killed half a billion people last century"},{"time":184000,"text":"and no longer is with us?"},{"time":186000,"text":"Or polio? How many of you remember the iron lung?"},{"time":189000,"text":"We don't see scenes like this anymore"},{"time":192000,"text":"because of vaccines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"Now, it's interesting"},{"time":196000,"text":"because there are 30-odd diseases"},{"time":199000,"text":"that can be treated with vaccines now,"},{"time":201000,"text":"but we're still threatened by things like HIV and flu."},{"time":204000,"text":"Why is that?"},{"time":206000,"text":"Well, here's the dirty little secret."},{"time":208000,"text":"Until recently, we haven't had to know"},{"time":210000,"text":"exactly how a vaccine worked."},{"time":213000,"text":"We knew they worked through old-fashioned trial and error."},{"time":216000,"text":"You took a pathogen, you modified it,"},{"time":218000,"text":"you injected it into a person or an animal"},{"time":221000,"text":"and you saw what happened."},{"time":223000,"text":"This worked well for most pathogens,"},{"time":226000,"text":"somewhat well for crafty bugs like flu,"},{"time":229000,"text":"but not at all for HIV,"},{"time":231000,"text":"for which humans have no natural immunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"So let's explore how vaccines work."},{"time":237000,"text":"They basically create a cache"},{"time":239000,"text":"of weapons for your immune system"},{"time":241000,"text":"which you can deploy when needed."},{"time":244000,"text":"Now, when you get a viral infection,"},{"time":247000,"text":"what normally happens is it takes days or weeks"},{"time":249000,"text":"for your body to fight back"},{"time":251000,"text":"at full strength,"},{"time":253000,"text":"and that might be too late."},{"time":255000,"text":"When you're pre-immunized,"},{"time":257000,"text":"what happens is you have forces in your body"},{"time":259000,"text":"pre-trained to recognize"},{"time":261000,"text":"and defeat specific foes."},{"time":263000,"text":"So that's really how vaccines work."},{"time":265000,"text":"Now, let's take a look at a video"},{"time":267000,"text":"that we're debuting at TED, for the first time,"},{"time":270000,"text":"on how an effective HIV vaccine might work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"Narrator: A vaccine trains the body in advance"},{"time":282000,"text":"how to recognize and neutralize"},{"time":284000,"text":"a specific invader."},{"time":286000,"text":"After HIV penetrates the body's mucosal barriers,"},{"time":289000,"text":"it infects immune cells to replicate."},{"time":293000,"text":"The invader draws the attention"},{"time":295000,"text":"of the immune system's front-line troops."},{"time":297000,"text":"Dendritic cells, or macrophages,"},{"time":299000,"text":"capture the virus and display pieces of it."},{"time":303000,"text":"Memory cells generated by the HIV vaccine"},{"time":306000,"text":"are activated when they learn"},{"time":308000,"text":"HIV is present from the front-line troops."},{"time":311000,"text":"These memory cells immediately deploy"},{"time":314000,"text":"the exact weapons needed."},{"time":317000,"text":"Memory B cells turn into plasma cells,"},{"time":320000,"text":"which produce wave after wave"},{"time":322000,"text":"of the specific antibodies"},{"time":324000,"text":"that latch onto HIV"},{"time":326000,"text":"to prevent it from infecting cells,"},{"time":328000,"text":"while squadrons of killer T cells"},{"time":330000,"text":"seek out and destroy cells"},{"time":332000,"text":"that are already HIV infected."},{"time":335000,"text":"The virus is defeated."},{"time":337000,"text":"Without a vaccine,"},{"time":339000,"text":"these responses would have taken more than a week."},{"time":342000,"text":"By that time, the battle against HIV"},{"time":344000,"text":"would already have been lost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"Seth Berkley: Really cool video, isn't it?"},{"time":356000,"text":"The antibodies you just saw in this video,"},{"time":359000,"text":"in action, are the ones that make most vaccines work."},{"time":362000,"text":"So the real question then is:"},{"time":364000,"text":"How do we ensure that your body makes"},{"time":366000,"text":"the exact ones that we need to protect"},{"time":368000,"text":"against flu and HIV?"},{"time":370000,"text":"The principal challenge for both of these viruses"},{"time":373000,"text":"is that they're always changing."},{"time":375000,"text":"So let's take a look at the flu virus."},{"time":378000,"text":"In this rendering of the flu virus,"},{"time":380000,"text":"these different colored spikes are what it uses to infect you."},{"time":383000,"text":"And also, what the antibodies use is a handle"},{"time":386000,"text":"to essentially grab and neutralize the virus."},{"time":389000,"text":"When these mutate, they change their shape,"},{"time":392000,"text":"and the antibodies don't know what they're looking at anymore."},{"time":395000,"text":"So that's why every year"},{"time":398000,"text":"you can catch a slightly different strain of flu."},{"time":401000,"text":"It's also why in the spring,"},{"time":403000,"text":"we have to make a best guess"},{"time":405000,"text":"at which three strains are going to prevail the next year,"},{"time":408000,"text":"put those into a single vaccine"},{"time":410000,"text":"and rush those into production for the fall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"Even worse,"},{"time":415000,"text":"the most common influenza -- influenza A --"},{"time":418000,"text":"also infects animals"},{"time":420000,"text":"that live in close proximity to humans,"},{"time":422000,"text":"and they can recombine"},{"time":424000,"text":"in those particular animals."},{"time":426000,"text":"In addition, wild aquatic birds"},{"time":428000,"text":"carry all known strains"},{"time":430000,"text":"of influenza."},{"time":432000,"text":"So, you've got this situation:"},{"time":434000,"text":"In 2003,"},{"time":436000,"text":"we had an H5N1 virus"},{"time":439000,"text":"that jumped from birds into humans"},{"time":442000,"text":"in a few isolated cases"},{"time":444000,"text":"with an apparent mortality rate of 70 percent."},{"time":447000,"text":"Now luckily, that particular virus,"},{"time":450000,"text":"although very scary at the time,"},{"time":452000,"text":"did not transmit from person to person"},{"time":454000,"text":"very easily."},{"time":456000,"text":"This year's H1N1 threat"},{"time":459000,"text":"was actually a human, avian, swine mixture"},{"time":463000,"text":"that arose in Mexico."},{"time":465000,"text":"It was easily transmitted,"},{"time":467000,"text":"but, luckily, was pretty mild."},{"time":470000,"text":"And so, in a sense,"},{"time":472000,"text":"our luck is holding out,"},{"time":474000,"text":"but you know, another wild bird could fly over at anytime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"Now let's take a look at HIV."},{"time":480000,"text":"As variable as flu is,"},{"time":482000,"text":"HIV makes flu"},{"time":484000,"text":"look like the Rock of Gibraltar."},{"time":486000,"text":"The virus that causes AIDS"},{"time":488000,"text":"is the trickiest pathogen"},{"time":490000,"text":"scientists have ever confronted."},{"time":492000,"text":"It mutates furiously,"},{"time":494000,"text":"it has decoys to evade the immune system,"},{"time":496000,"text":"it attacks the very cells that are trying to fight it"},{"time":499000,"text":"and it quickly hides itself"},{"time":501000,"text":"in your genome."},{"time":503000,"text":"Here's a slide looking at"},{"time":505000,"text":"the genetic variation of flu"},{"time":507000,"text":"and comparing that to HIV,"},{"time":509000,"text":"a much wilder target."},{"time":512000,"text":"In the video a moment ago,"},{"time":514000,"text":"you saw fleets of new viruses launching from infected cells."},{"time":517000,"text":"Now realize that in a recently infected person,"},{"time":520000,"text":"there are millions of these ships;"},{"time":522000,"text":"each one is just slightly different."},{"time":524000,"text":"Finding a weapon that recognizes"},{"time":526000,"text":"and sinks all of them"},{"time":528000,"text":"makes the job that much harder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"Now, in the 27 years since HIV"},{"time":533000,"text":"was identified as the cause of AIDS,"},{"time":536000,"text":"we've developed more drugs to treat HIV"},{"time":538000,"text":"than all other viruses put together."},{"time":541000,"text":"These drugs aren't cures,"},{"time":543000,"text":"but they represent a huge triumph of science"},{"time":545000,"text":"because they take away the automatic death sentence"},{"time":547000,"text":"from a diagnosis of HIV,"},{"time":549000,"text":"at least for those who can access them."},{"time":552000,"text":"The vaccine effort though is really quite different."},{"time":555000,"text":"Large companies moved away from it"},{"time":557000,"text":"because they thought the science was so difficult"},{"time":560000,"text":"and vaccines were seen as poor business."},{"time":563000,"text":"Many thought that it was just impossible to make an AIDS vaccine,"},{"time":566000,"text":"but today, evidence tells us otherwise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569000,"text":"In September,"},{"time":571000,"text":"we had surprising but exciting findings"},{"time":574000,"text":"from a clinical trial that took place in Thailand."},{"time":577000,"text":"For the first time, we saw an AIDS vaccine work in humans --"},{"time":580000,"text":"albeit, quite modestly --"},{"time":583000,"text":"and that particular vaccine was made"},{"time":585000,"text":"almost a decade ago."},{"time":587000,"text":"Newer concepts and early testing now"},{"time":589000,"text":"show even greater promise in the best of our animal models."},{"time":594000,"text":"But in the past few months, researchers have also isolated"},{"time":597000,"text":"several new broadly neutralizing antibodies"},{"time":600000,"text":"from the blood of an HIV infected individual."},{"time":603000,"text":"Now, what does this mean?"},{"time":605000,"text":"We saw earlier that HIV"},{"time":607000,"text":"is highly variable,"},{"time":609000,"text":"that a broad neutralizing antibody"},{"time":611000,"text":"latches on and disables"},{"time":613000,"text":"multiple variations of the virus."},{"time":616000,"text":"If you take these and you put them"},{"time":618000,"text":"in the best of our monkey models,"},{"time":620000,"text":"they provide full protection from infection."},{"time":623000,"text":"In addition, these researchers found"},{"time":625000,"text":"a new site on HIV"},{"time":627000,"text":"where the antibodies can grab onto,"},{"time":629000,"text":"and what's so special about this spot"},{"time":631000,"text":"is that it changes very little"},{"time":633000,"text":"as the virus mutates."},{"time":635000,"text":"It's like, as many times"},{"time":637000,"text":"as the virus changes its clothes,"},{"time":639000,"text":"it's still wearing the same socks,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and now our job is to make sure"},{"time":643000,"text":"we get the body to really hate those socks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"So what we've got is a situation."},{"time":648000,"text":"The Thai results tell us"},{"time":650000,"text":"we can make an AIDS vaccine,"},{"time":652000,"text":"and the antibody findings"},{"time":654000,"text":"tell us how we might do that."},{"time":656000,"text":"This strategy, working backwards"},{"time":659000,"text":"from an antibody to create a vaccine candidate,"},{"time":661000,"text":"has never been done before in vaccine research."},{"time":664000,"text":"It's called retro-vaccinology,"},{"time":667000,"text":"and its implications extend"},{"time":669000,"text":"way beyond that of just HIV."},{"time":672000,"text":"So think of it this way."},{"time":674000,"text":"We've got these new antibodies we've identified,"},{"time":677000,"text":"and we know that they latch onto many, many variations of the virus."},{"time":680000,"text":"We know that they have to latch onto a specific part,"},{"time":683000,"text":"so if we can figure out the precise structure of that part,"},{"time":686000,"text":"present that through a vaccine,"},{"time":688000,"text":"what we hope is we can prompt"},{"time":690000,"text":"your immune system to make these matching antibodies."},{"time":693000,"text":"And that would create"},{"time":695000,"text":"a universal HIV vaccine."},{"time":697000,"text":"Now, it sounds easier than it is"},{"time":699000,"text":"because the structure actually looks more like"},{"time":701000,"text":"this blue antibody diagram"},{"time":703000,"text":"attached to its yellow binding site,"},{"time":705000,"text":"and as you can imagine, these three-dimensional structures"},{"time":707000,"text":"are much harder to work on."},{"time":709000,"text":"And if you guys have ideas to help us solve this,"},{"time":711000,"text":"we'd love to hear about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"But, you know, the research that has occurred from HIV now"},{"time":716000,"text":"has really helped with innovation with other diseases."},{"time":719000,"text":"So for instance, a biotechnology company"},{"time":721000,"text":"has now found broadly neutralizing"},{"time":723000,"text":"antibodies to influenza,"},{"time":725000,"text":"as well as a new antibody target on the flu virus."},{"time":728000,"text":"They're currently making a cocktail --"},{"time":731000,"text":"an antibody cocktail -- that can be used to treat"},{"time":734000,"text":"severe, overwhelming cases of flu."},{"time":737000,"text":"In the longer term, what they can do"},{"time":739000,"text":"is use these tools of retro-vaccinology"},{"time":741000,"text":"to make a preventive flu vaccine."},{"time":744000,"text":"Now, retro-vaccinology is just one technique"},{"time":747000,"text":"within the ambit of so-called rational vaccine design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"Let me give you another example."},{"time":753000,"text":"We talked about before the H and N spikes"},{"time":755000,"text":"on the surface of the flu virus."},{"time":757000,"text":"Notice these other, smaller protuberances."},{"time":760000,"text":"These are largely hidden from the immune system."},{"time":763000,"text":"Now it turns out that these spots"},{"time":765000,"text":"also don't change much when the virus mutates."},{"time":768000,"text":"If you can cripple these with specific antibodies,"},{"time":770000,"text":"you could cripple all versions of the flu."},{"time":773000,"text":"So far, animal tests indicate"},{"time":775000,"text":"that such a vaccine could prevent severe disease,"},{"time":778000,"text":"although you might get a mild case."},{"time":780000,"text":"So if this works in humans, what we're talking about"},{"time":783000,"text":"is a universal flu vaccine,"},{"time":785000,"text":"one that doesn't need to change every year"},{"time":787000,"text":"and would remove the threat of death."},{"time":790000,"text":"We really could think of flu, then,"},{"time":792000,"text":"as just a bad cold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795000,"text":"Of course, the best vaccine imaginable"},{"time":797000,"text":"is only valuable to the extent"},{"time":799000,"text":"we get it to everyone who needs it."},{"time":801000,"text":"So to do that, we have to combine"},{"time":803000,"text":"smart vaccine design with smart production methods"},{"time":806000,"text":"and, of course, smart delivery methods."},{"time":809000,"text":"So I want you to think back a few months ago."},{"time":811000,"text":"In June, the World Health Organization"},{"time":814000,"text":"declared the first global"},{"time":816000,"text":"flu pandemic in 41 years."},{"time":818000,"text":"The U.S. government promised"},{"time":820000,"text":"150 million doses of vaccine"},{"time":822000,"text":"by October 15th for the flu peak."},{"time":824000,"text":"Vaccines were promised to developing countries."},{"time":826000,"text":"Hundreds of millions of dollars were spent"},{"time":828000,"text":"and flowed to accelerating vaccine manufacturing."},{"time":831000,"text":"So what happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":833000,"text":"Well, we first figured out"},{"time":835000,"text":"how to make flu vaccines, how to produce them,"},{"time":838000,"text":"in the early 1940s."},{"time":840000,"text":"It was a slow, cumbersome process"},{"time":843000,"text":"that depended on chicken eggs,"},{"time":846000,"text":"millions of living chicken eggs."},{"time":849000,"text":"Viruses only grow in living things,"},{"time":851000,"text":"and so it turned out that, for flu,"},{"time":853000,"text":"chicken eggs worked really well."},{"time":855000,"text":"For most strains, you could get one to two doses"},{"time":858000,"text":"of vaccine per egg."},{"time":860000,"text":"Luckily for us,"},{"time":862000,"text":"we live in an era of breathtaking"},{"time":864000,"text":"biomedical advances."},{"time":866000,"text":"So today, we get our flu vaccines from ..."},{"time":869000,"text":"chicken eggs,"},{"time":871000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":873000,"text":"hundreds of millions of chicken eggs."},{"time":875000,"text":"Almost nothing has changed."},{"time":877000,"text":"The system is reliable"},{"time":879000,"text":"but the problem is you never know how well"},{"time":881000,"text":"a strain is going to grow."},{"time":884000,"text":"This year's swine flu strain"},{"time":886000,"text":"grew very poorly in early production:"},{"time":889000,"text":"basically .6 doses per egg."},{"time":893000,"text":"So, here's an alarming thought."},{"time":895000,"text":"What if that wild bird flies by again?"},{"time":897000,"text":"You could see an avian strain"},{"time":899000,"text":"that would infect the poultry flocks,"},{"time":901000,"text":"and then we would have no eggs for our vaccines."},{"time":903000,"text":"So, Dan [Barber], if you want"},{"time":905000,"text":"billions of chicken pellets"},{"time":907000,"text":"for your fish farm,"},{"time":909000,"text":"I know where to get them."},{"time":911000,"text":"So right now, the world can produce"},{"time":913000,"text":"about 350 million doses"},{"time":915000,"text":"of flu vaccine for the three strains,"},{"time":918000,"text":"and we can up that to about 1.2 billion doses"},{"time":921000,"text":"if we want to target a single variant"},{"time":923000,"text":"like swine flu."},{"time":925000,"text":"But this assumes that our factories are humming"},{"time":928000,"text":"because, in 2004,"},{"time":930000,"text":"the U.S. supply was cut in half"},{"time":932000,"text":"by contamination at one single plant."},{"time":935000,"text":"And the process still takes"},{"time":937000,"text":"more than half a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939000,"text":"So are we better prepared"},{"time":941000,"text":"than we were in 1918?"},{"time":943000,"text":"Well, with the new technologies emerging now,"},{"time":945000,"text":"I hope we can say definitively, \"Yes.\""},{"time":947000,"text":"Imagine we could produce enough flu vaccine"},{"time":950000,"text":"for everyone in the entire world"},{"time":953000,"text":"for less than half of what we're currently spending"},{"time":955000,"text":"now in the United States."},{"time":957000,"text":"With a range of new technologies, we could."},{"time":960000,"text":"Here's an example:"},{"time":962000,"text":"A company I'm engaged with has found"},{"time":964000,"text":"a specific piece of the H spike of flu"},{"time":966000,"text":"that sparks the immune system."},{"time":968000,"text":"If you lop this off and attach it"},{"time":970000,"text":"to the tail of a different bacterium,"},{"time":973000,"text":"which creates a vigorous immune response,"},{"time":975000,"text":"they've created a very powerful flu fighter."},{"time":977000,"text":"This vaccine is so small"},{"time":979000,"text":"it can be grown in a common bacteria, E. coli."},{"time":982000,"text":"Now, as you know, bacteria reproduce quickly --"},{"time":985000,"text":"it's like making yogurt --"},{"time":987000,"text":"and so we could produce enough swine origin flu"},{"time":989000,"text":"for the entire world in a few factories, in a few weeks,"},{"time":992000,"text":"with no eggs,"},{"time":994000,"text":"for a fraction of the cost of current methods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002000,"text":"So here's a comparison of several of these new vaccine technologies."},{"time":1005000,"text":"And, aside from the radically increased production"},{"time":1008000,"text":"and huge cost savings --"},{"time":1010000,"text":"for example, the E. coli method I just talked about --"},{"time":1013000,"text":"look at the time saved: this would be lives saved."},{"time":1016000,"text":"The developing world,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"mostly left out of the current response,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"sees the potential of these alternate technologies"},{"time":1024000,"text":"and they're leapfrogging the West."},{"time":1026000,"text":"India, Mexico and others are already"},{"time":1028000,"text":"making experimental flu vaccines,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"and they may be the first place"},{"time":1032000,"text":"we see these vaccines in use."},{"time":1034000,"text":"Because these technologies are so efficient"},{"time":1037000,"text":"and relatively cheap,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"billions of people can have access to lifesaving vaccines"},{"time":1042000,"text":"if we can figure out how to deliver them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044000,"text":"Now think of where this leads us."},{"time":1046000,"text":"New infectious diseases"},{"time":1048000,"text":"appear or reappear"},{"time":1050000,"text":"every few years."},{"time":1052000,"text":"Some day, perhaps soon,"},{"time":1054000,"text":"we'll have a virus that is going to threaten all of us."},{"time":1057000,"text":"Will we be quick enough to react"},{"time":1059000,"text":"before millions die?"},{"time":1061000,"text":"Luckily, this year's flu was relatively mild."},{"time":1064000,"text":"I say, \"luckily\" in part"},{"time":1066000,"text":"because virtually no one in the developing world"},{"time":1069000,"text":"was vaccinated."},{"time":1071000,"text":"So if we have the political and financial foresight"},{"time":1074000,"text":"to sustain our investments,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"we will master these and new tools of vaccinology,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"and with these tools we can produce"},{"time":1081000,"text":"enough vaccine for everyone at low cost"},{"time":1083000,"text":"and ensure healthy productive lives."},{"time":1086000,"text":"No longer must flu have to kill half a million people a year."},{"time":1089000,"text":"No longer does AIDS"},{"time":1091000,"text":"need to kill two million a year."},{"time":1093000,"text":"No longer do the poor and vulnerable"},{"time":1095000,"text":"need to be threatened by infectious diseases,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"or indeed, anybody."},{"time":1100000,"text":"Instead of having Vaclav Smil's"},{"time":1103000,"text":"\"massively fatal discontinuity\" of life,"},{"time":1106000,"text":"we can ensure"},{"time":1108000,"text":"the continuity of life."},{"time":1110000,"text":"What the world needs now are these new vaccines,"},{"time":1112000,"text":"and we can make it happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1114000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you."},{"time":1126000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1132000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1134000,"text":"So, the science is changing."},{"time":1137000,"text":"In your mind, Seth -- I mean, you must dream about this --"},{"time":1140000,"text":"what is the kind of time scale"},{"time":1143000,"text":"on, let's start with HIV,"},{"time":1145000,"text":"for a game-changing vaccine that's actually out there and usable?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1149000,"text":"SB: The game change can come at any time,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"because the problem we have now is"},{"time":1153000,"text":"we've shown we can get a vaccine to work in humans;"},{"time":1155000,"text":"we just need a better one."},{"time":1157000,"text":"And with these types of antibodies, we know humans can make them."},{"time":1159000,"text":"So, if we can figure out how to do that,"},{"time":1161000,"text":"then we have the vaccine,"},{"time":1163000,"text":"and what's interesting is there already is"},{"time":1165000,"text":"some evidence that we're beginning to crack that problem."},{"time":1167000,"text":"So, the challenge is full speed ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1169000,"text":"CA: In your gut, do you think it's probably going to be at least another five years?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171000,"text":"SB: You know, everybody says it's 10 years,"},{"time":1173000,"text":"but it's been 10 years every 10 years."},{"time":1175000,"text":"So I hate to put a timeline"},{"time":1177000,"text":"on scientific innovation,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"but the investments that have occurred are now paying dividends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1182000,"text":"CA: And that's the same with universal flu vaccine, the same kind of thing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1185000,"text":"SB: I think flu is different. I think what happened with flu is"},{"time":1187000,"text":"we've got a bunch -- I just showed some of this --"},{"time":1189000,"text":"a bunch of really cool and useful technologies that are ready to go now."},{"time":1192000,"text":"They look good. The problem has been that,"},{"time":1194000,"text":"what we did is we invested in traditional technologies"},{"time":1197000,"text":"because that's what we were comfortable with."},{"time":1199000,"text":"You also can use adjuvants, which are chemicals you mix."},{"time":1202000,"text":"That's what Europe is doing, so we could have diluted out"},{"time":1204000,"text":"our supply of flu and made more available,"},{"time":1206000,"text":"but, going back to what Michael Specter said,"},{"time":1209000,"text":"the anti-vaccine crowd didn't really want that to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1212000,"text":"CA: And malaria's even further behind?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1214000,"text":"SB: No, malaria, there is a candidate"},{"time":1216000,"text":"that actually showed efficacy in an earlier trial"},{"time":1219000,"text":"and is currently in phase three trials now."},{"time":1221000,"text":"It probably isn't the perfect vaccine, but it's moving along."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1224000,"text":"CA: Seth, most of us do work where every month,"},{"time":1226000,"text":"we produce something;"},{"time":1228000,"text":"we get that kind of gratification."},{"time":1230000,"text":"You've been slaving away at this for more than a decade,"},{"time":1233000,"text":"and I salute you and your colleagues for what you do."},{"time":1236000,"text":"The world needs people like you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1238000,"text":"SB: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1240000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}